Installing FTP Servers : sudo apt install vsftpd
                         sudo apt install proftpd -y
                         sudo apt install pure-ftpd -y

  Connecting to an FTP Server: ftp ip

  get filename
• Downloads a file from the FTP server to the local client machine.

put filename
• Uploads a file from the local client machine to the FTP server.


ASCII Mode
• Used for text files.
• Transfers data line by line.
• Automatically converts line endings (Linux ↔ Windows).
• Suitable for files like: .txt,.html,.csv,.log

FTP command: ascii

Binary (BIN) Mode
• Used for non-text (binary) files.
• Transfers data exactly as it is, with no modification.
• Prevents file corruption.
• Suitable for files like:.zip,.exe,.jpg,.png,.mp3,.pdf

FTP command: binary or bin
